# KVM Virtualization Deployment & Configuration Guide

**Author:** Hridoy
**Platform:** Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS
**Virtualization Stack:** KVM + QEMU + libvirt
**Management Tools:** Cockpit, virt-manager
**Remote Access:** SSH via MobaXterm (X11 Forwarding)

---

# Overview

This repository documents the **deployment and configuration of a KVM-based virtualization environment** running on **Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS**.

The goal of this project is to build a **Linux-based virtualization host** capable of running multiple virtual machines and managing them remotely using both:

* **Cockpit Web Interface**
* **virt-manager GUI**

The environment is managed remotely through **SSH using MobaXterm with X11 forwarding**, allowing GUI tools to run from a headless server.

This project demonstrates how KVM can be deployed as a **powerful open-source alternative to traditional hypervisors**.

