# System Preparation

Update system packages:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

Install virtualization capability checker:

```bash
sudo apt install cpu-checker
```

Verify CPU virtualization support:

```bash
kvm-ok
```

Expected output:

```
INFO: /dev/kvm exists
KVM acceleration can be used
```

---

# Installing KVM Virtualization Stack

Install the required KVM packages:

```bash
sudo apt install qemu-kvm \
libvirt-daemon-system \
libvirt-clients \
bridge-utils \
virtinst \
virt-viewer -y
```

### Package Description

| Package               | Purpose                          |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| qemu-kvm              | Virtual machine execution engine |
| libvirt-daemon-system | Virtualization daemon            |
| libvirt-clients       | CLI virtualization tools         |
| bridge-utils          | Network bridge utilities         |
| virtinst              | VM installation tools            |
| virt-viewer           | VM graphical console viewer      |

